TouristPlaces.Name: Gateway Of India Mumbai
TouristPlaces.Description: Grand, Indo-Saracenic-style, 26m-tall triumphal stone arch, built on the waterfront in 1924.

TouristPlaces.Name: Kanheri Caves
TouristPlaces.Description: Ancient temples, hewn from rock, with Buddhist shrines, paintings of Buddha and 109 entrances.

TouristPlaces.Name: Marine Drive
TouristPlaces.Description: Bayside walkway named for the effect of its night-time lights, with snack vendors under palm trees.

TouristPlaces.Name: Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Vastu Sangrahalaya
TouristPlaces.Description: Grand museum with Indo-Saracenic architecture featuring history exhibits, cultural art & education.

TouristPlaces.Name: Love Mumbai
TouristPlaces.Description: Giant lettering popular for photo opportunities on a waterfront promenade with city skyline views.

TouristPlaces.Name: Hanging Gardens
TouristPlaces.Description: Tranquil garden offering views of the Arabian Sea, flowers & hedges sculpted into animal shapes.

TouristPlaces.Name: Mahakali Caves
TouristPlaces.Description: Stone monastery caves carved from rock are the focus of this ancient archeological site.

TouristPlaces.Name: Sanjay Gandhi National Park
TouristPlaces.Description: Sprawling, forested park home to the ancient Kanheri Caves, a lion & tiger safari & nature trails.

TouristPlaces.Name: Flora Fountain
TouristPlaces.Description: A sculpture of the Roman goddess Flora sits atop this prominent fountain built in 1864.

TouristPlaces.Name: Dr. Bhau Daji Lad Museum
TouristPlaces.Description: Mumbai's first museum showcasing the city's cultural heritage with artistic & decorative artifacts.

TouristPlaces.Name: Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Park
TouristPlaces.Description: Created in 1925, the city's largest park houses cricket & soccer clubs, plus a pool & walking paths.
